Q: Flutter ImageFilter.blur is gone when scrolling to beginning or end of list A: <p>I've had this happen to me before. I'm assuming the Padding is the child of body, wrap your scrollable with this and make it the child of your padding. If that doesn't work, move it around your widget tree until it does.</p>
<pre><code>NotificationListener&lt;OverscrollIndicatorNotification&gt;(
    onNotification: (overscroll) {
      overscroll.disallowIndicator();
      return true;
    },
    child: your builder here 
</code></pre>
<p>So it should look like this:</p>
<pre><code>Padding(
  padding: const EdgeInsets.only(bottom: 12.0, left: 0.0),
  child: SizedBox(
    height: 120,
    child: NotificationListener&lt;OverscrollIndicatorNotification&gt;(
    onNotification: (overscroll) {
      overscroll.disallowIndicator();
      return true;
    },
